Your function takes a `std::string` by value, so every time you call the function, a new `string` must be created for it.  To create a new `std::string` from a piece of another `std::string`, use the [`std::string::substr()`](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/string/basic_string/substr) method.

Also, `std::string` is not a null-terminated string, you should be looping based on its `size()` instead of its characters:

```c++
void someFunction(node * root, string s)
