Angular provides us with environment.ts and environment.prod.ts files, you can utilize them like this- 


 

 

      // environment.ts
      export const environment = {
      production: false,
      baseUrl: &#39;http://localhost:3000/get/info&#39;  
    };
     // environment.prod.ts
      export const environment = {
      production: true,
      baseUrl: &#39;http://mydomainname.com/get/info&#39;  
    };

ng build --prod will use base url from environment.prod.ts, and locally base url from environment.ts will be used.

You can import environment file where you need to make api calls in your application, and use baseUrl from it.

